myapp.GUIfx.Bike

Class BikeController

  • java.lang.Object
    • myapp.GUIfx.Bike.BikeController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.fxml.Initializable

    public class BikeController
extends java.lang.Object
implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
    The BikeController class is the controller of BikePane.fxml. This class contains methodes to add a new bike, edit/delete bikes, show status about a bike, show all repairs, show the bike in a map and a list of all bikes.
    Author:
    Sara Hjelle, Martin Moan created the map functions.

      • closeAll

        public void closeAll()
        closeAll() closes all the panes inside the main bike pane. This method makes it easy to open other panes, without having to set all the panes visibility to false each time.

      • findBike

        public Bike findBike(int bikeId)
        This method goes through the list of bikes and compares the bikeID from the list to the id that is sent in as a parameter. If there is a match this method returns the bike with the same id.
        Parameters:
        bikeId - the id you want to find the corresponding bike to.
        Returns:
        returns a Bike object if a match is found, null if there is no match.
